      • greaterOrEqual

        public boolean greaterOrEqual(GMS gms)
        If all components (gas, minerals, supply) of this value are non-negative, returns true if all are >= that of the given value. If a component is negative, returns false if the given value's component is >= 0.
        Usually all components are >= 0 and this can be used to check if a price could be payed now.
        If planning ahead is used, components could already be negative. But if the cost (ie. supply) is 0, it might still be possible to purchase it immediately.
